      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The straight-line depreciation formula is: **Depreciation Expense = (Cost − Salvage Value) ÷ Useful Life**. Plugging in your numbers, you get **(50,000 − 5,000) ÷ 5**, which equals **9,000** per year. So, for each of the five years, you will record a depreciation expense of $9,000 on your accounting records.",
      "source": "target",
